  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators want to investigate whether sunscreen is removed by clothing and to what
      extend when the amount of sunscreen applied varies.Does clothing reduce the SPF when clothes
      are put on 20, 8, or 4 minutes after sunscreen application? The investigators also want to
      investigate the persistence of sunscreen during eight hours indoor. How much does the SPF
      reduces? Furthermore, we want to investigate whether sunscreen in the layers 2, 1, and 0.5
      mg/cm2 reduce the vitamin D production in the skin.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
